headline: The 5 Most Interesting Analyst Questions From Conagra’s Q4 Earnings Call
summary: Conagra’s fourth quarter was marked by weaker sales volumes and a significant drop in operating margin, with the market reacting negatively to the results. Management attributed the year-over-year sales decline to persistent supply constraints in frozen foods, delayed seasonal demand, and a competitive promotional environment. CEO Sean Connolly noted that, “Our goal this quarter in Frozen was to reclaim the market share that we basically loaned out to a competitor when we had supply constraints
